    <note>Zhou(1) Shihou [2120] E's [7194] father, Fan(2) Zhongwen's [7214] son-in-law, Chen(1) Guan(2)'s [7128] father-in-law. One son became a Buddhist monk. Lou Yue in his funerary inscriptions for Shihou's great grandsons, Mo [16541] (q.v.) and Ji(2) [16540] (q.v.) identifies his father-in-law as Fan(2) Zhongyan, which is demonstrably incorrect. Zhejiang TZ, 123.28a has jinshi in 1057 (date used); XCB, 267.2b; Zou Hao, WJ, 37.11a (wife, born Fan, who died in 1109 at age 79). CBD, 2, 1483.</note>
